passages.text:
{Player-Rugged Man-null-true-1-null}
What do you mean? 

[[You aren't with Them]]

{Player-Rugged Man-intelligence <= 4-true-1-null}
Meat? I'm hungry and I want meat. Every time I try to catch an animal it runs away. Can I have some of yours? 

[[Have you tried shooting it?]]

{Player-Rugged Man-charisma >= 6-true-1-null}
And we’ve got a lot of people to feed over there. Either you give us what we need or things could happen to someone. 


[[Don't Hurt Me]]

{Player-Rugged Man- charisma < 6-true-1-null}
And we’re… uh… very hungry and want food. Give us the food or we will… hurt you!

[[How about no]]

{Narrator-Player-null-false-1-null}
There is no response from the door when you knock. 

[[Leave]]

{Narrator-Player-hasFireBoltSpell-true-1-fightRuggedHunter}
Wood is meant to be burned, right? With a modicum of concentration, flames erupt from your open palm. Concentrating the fire down into a small orb, you stand back and lob the projectile at the door. The fireball explodes on impact, creating a small hole in the wood that smoulders with latent embers. 

You can easily reach the other side of the doorknob now. You reach in, unlocking the door and swing it open to reveal its terrified occupant. He readies a knife he had holstered on his hip and takes a step forward. You ready yourself for combat.

{Narrator-Player-strength >= 8-true-1-fightRuggedHunter}
You assume an agressive stance and charge at the door, slamming into it with the might of a bull. It rocks on its hinges once, twice, then gives way to its terrified occupant.

He draws a short knife from his waist and gets ready for combat. With no other option left, you join him.

{Narrator-Player-hasForceBurstSpell-true-1-fightRuggedHunter}
The door is sturdy enough, but with an adequate amount of force one can break down any door, and you happen to have quite the forceful spell memorized. You chant a quiet prayer under your breath, and gather the winds of Beltyr. All at once you release the pent up energy in a massive burst, sending the door flying off of its hinges and into the cabin. 

The man inside draws a knife from his waist and readies himself for combat. You do the same.

{Narrator-Player-hasThunderBoltSpell-true-1-fightRuggedHunter}
An image springs to your mind as you gaze upon the door, one of a tree cleaved clean in half by a bolt of lightning. You smile, and begin to charge up electricity in your fingertips. Pointing them at your target, you release a bolt of lightning at the door causing the very fibers of the material to explode in a thousand directions. The smell of ozone is in the air.

The man inside hastily draws a knife from his waist and readies himself for combat. You do the same.

{Player-Rugged Man-intelligence <= 4-true-1-null}
Yea but they move too quick. It's not fair, they should stand still like the straw targets do.

[[Please go Away]]

{Player-Rugged Man-intelligence <= 4-true-1-null}
No, bows hurt my arm and crossbows are too hard to load.

[[Please go Away]]

{Rugged Man-Player-null-true-1-null}
By the 7... Look kid. How about this, I give you some food, some nice tasty meat, and you go along and have a good time out in the nice forest far away from me. Would you do that?

[[Yay food]]

{Player-Rugged Man-intelligence <= 4-true-1-null}
Ok!

[[Leave]]

{Rugged Man-Player-null-true-1-null}
You aren't with them, are you? Those conniving, back-stabbing, chunks of horse excrement!

[[Who?]]

{Player-Rugged Man-null-true-1-null}
Who are you talking about?

[[The Bandits]]

{Player-Rugged Man-null-true-1-null}
Where are these bandits located?

[[Where they are]]

{Player-Rugged Man-null-true-1-null}
How many of them do you think there are?

[[How Many]]

{Player-Rugged Man-strength >= 6-true-1-null}
But you're still breathing, which means you still have something left to live for. Hand it over.

[[Don't Hurt Me]]

{Rugged Man-Player-null-true-1-null}
Or, hypothetically, I could instead do this:

[[He does This]]

{Rugged Man-Player-charisma >= 6-true-1-null}
Wait, there's no need to be hasty! I've got a few things lying around that I don't really need... that much... Here, take this bundle of furs I've been saving. They should fetch a good price!

[[Take the Furs]]

{Player-Rugged Man- strength < 6-true-1-null}
Oh yea, well I want your stuff and I'm gonna take it if you don't give it to me!

[[How about no]]

{Player-Rugged Man-null-true-1-null}
Those bandits need to go. I'll take them out for you, don't worry.

[[Good Luck]]

{Rugged Man-Player-null-true-1-null}
That's a good joke lad. Now, I've done enough talking for the day. You best be on your way. 
[[Now Leave]]

{Narrator-Player-strength < 8-true-1-fightRuggedHunter}
Try as you might, the door just won't seem to budge. Worse still, the noise you made seems to have alerted the occupant of the cabin. You hear another bolt click into place as another lock on the door latches shut. Whatever hope you had of breaking down the door before is gone now.

[[Leave]]

{Narrator-Player-null-true-1-null}
You knock on the door. After a moment of silence the door swings open to reveal a rugged man of middle age. Before you can take in any more details he barks out:

[[Knock]]
